@database "ALE"
@master ""ALE"."1""
@remark "manual page source format generated by PolyglotMan v3.2 available at http://polyglotman.sourceforge.net/"
@wordwrap
@tab 8
    
@node sect0 "Name"
ale - a synthetic capture engine and renderer 
@endnode

@node sect1 "Synopsis"
@{b}ale@{ub} [@{i}OPTIONS@{ui}] @{i}original-frame@{ui} [@{i}supplemental-frames@{ui} ...] @{i}output-file@{ui} @{b}ale@{ub} [@{i}HELP OPTIONS@{ui}] @{b}ale --version@{ub} 
@endnode

@node sect2 "Description"
@{b}ALE@{ub} is a free software synthetic capture engine and renderer accepting, as input, a sequence of image frames, and producing, as output, rendered images, registration data, and 3D models (currently experimental). 
@endnode

@node sect3 "Examples"
@{b}ale --hu@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Print the help page on program usage. @{lindent 0}


@{b}ale 001.ppm 002.ppm 003.ppm out.ppm@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Render output file @{b}out.ppm@{ub} from inputs @{b}001.ppm@{ub}, @{b}002.ppm@{ub}, and @{b}003.ppm@{ub}. @{lindent 0}


@{b}ale --scale 2 001.ppm 002.ppm 003.ppm out.png@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Render output file @{b}out.png@{ub} at 2x scale. @{lindent 0}


@{b}ale --perturb-upper=0 --trans-load=a.t --projective frame*.png out.png@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Render output file @{b}out.png@{ub} from inputs @{b}frame*.png@{ub}, using projective transformations as described in the file @{b}a.t@{ub}. @{lindent 0}


@{b}ale --3dv 0 out.png --projective frame*.png null:@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Render output file @{b}out.png@{ub} from inputs @{b}frame*.png@{ub}, using a 3D scene model to determine transformations. @{lindent 0}


@{b}ale --visp last:sinc*lanc:6 sf:0 out/ .jpg in/*.jpg null:@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Render a video stream from files @{b}in/*.jpg@{ub} to the directory @{b}out/@{ub}, stabilizing to the first frame, with a lanczos-windowed sinc filter. @{lindent 0}



@endnode

@node sect4 "Usage"
@{b}ale@{ub} is a wrapper script that calls the executable @{b}ale-bin@{ub} after extracting exposure EXIF information from image files (when the @{b}exiftool@{ub} utility is available) and converting from raw formats (when the @{b}dcraw@{ub} utility is available). When @{b}ale-bin@{ub} has been linked with ImageMagick, input and output files may be of any kind supported by ImageMagick. Otherwise, only PPM files can be read and written by @{b}ale-bin@{ub}. 
@endnode

@node sect5 "Options"
@{i}OPTIONS@{ui} are summarized via built-in help pages (see @{b}HELP OPTIONS@{ub} below). More detailed manuals describing options and internal algorithms are available for certain versions of ALE. See @{b}SEE ALSO@{ub} below for more details on other manuals. 
@endnode

@node sect6 "Help Options"
A listing of available help options can be obtained by invoking @{b}ale --hu@{ub}. 
@endnode

@node sect7 "Environment"
The wrapper script @{b}ale@{ub} recognizes the following environment variables: @{b}ALE_BIN@{ub} @{lindent 3}
ALE executable to use. @{lindent 0}


@{b}DCRAW@{ub} @{lindent 3}
dcraw raw extraction tool to use. @{lindent 0}


@{b}EXIF_UTILITY@{ub} @{lindent 3}
EXIF extraction utility to use. @{lindent 0}


@{b}ALE_COUNT_THREADS@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Displays statistics on thread counts when set to a non-zero value. @{lindent 0}


@{b}PAGER@{ub} @{lindent 3}
Text pager to use (e.g., for displaying help pages). @{lindent 0}



@endnode

@node sect8 "See Also"
More detailed manuals for certain versions of ALE are distributed with source packages, and may also be available from: http://auricle.dyndns.org/ALE/manuals/ 
@endnode
